# Development Environment Configuration (Local Override)
# 
# This file provides examples for local development environment overrides.
# Copy this file to .env.development.local and adjust values as needed.
#
# IMPORTANT: .env.development.local is gitignored and will not be committed.
# This allows each developer to have their own local configuration.

# =============================================================================
# API Configuration
# =============================================================================

# Backend API Base URL
# 
# When to use proxy (RECOMMENDED for local development):
# - Leave this commented out or remove it entirely
# - The dev server will use the proxy configured in package.json
# - Automatically forwards /api/* requests to http://localhost:8080/api/*
# - No CORS issues in development
# - Simulates production-like environment
#
# When to use direct API URL:
# - Uncomment and set this variable when connecting to a remote backend
# - Useful for testing against staging or shared development servers
# - Requires backend to have proper CORS configuration
# - Backend must allow origin: http://localhost:3001
#
# Examples:
# REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/api          # Local backend (direct)
# REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=https://api-staging.example.com/api  # Staging server
# REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=https://api-dev.example.com/api      # Shared dev server

# Uncomment to override the default proxy behavior:
# REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/api

# =============================================================================
# Development Server Configuration
# =============================================================================

# Port for the development server
# Default: 3001 (configured in package.json)
# Uncomment to use a different port:
# PORT=3002

# Browser auto-open behavior
# Default: none (disabled in package.json)
# Uncomment to enable auto-opening browser:
# BROWSER=chrome
# BROWSER=firefox
# BROWSER=default

# =============================================================================
# Feature Flags (if applicable)
# =============================================================================

# Enable performance debug overlay
# REACT_APP_ENABLE_PERFORMANCE_DEBUG=true

# Enable verbose API logging
# REACT_APP_ENABLE_API_DEBUG=true

# =============================================================================
# Notes
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Proxy vs Direct API URL Decision Tree:
#
#    Are you developing locally with backend on localhost:8080?
#    ‚îú‚îÄ YES ‚Üí Use proxy (don't set REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL)
#    ‚îÇ        ‚úÖ No CORS issues
#    ‚îÇ        ‚úÖ Simpler setup
#    ‚îÇ        ‚úÖ Recommended
#    ‚îÇ
#    ‚îî‚îÄ NO ‚Üí Set REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL to your backend URL
#             ‚ö†Ô∏è  Backend must have CORS configured
#             ‚ö†Ô∏è  Must allow origin: http://localhost:3001
#             üìñ See BACKEND_CORS_SETUP.md for backend configuration
#
# 2. After changing environment variables:
#    - Restart the dev server (npm start)
#    - Environment variables are embedded at build time
#    - Changes won't take effect until restart
#
# 3. Troubleshooting:
#    - If you see CORS errors, verify backend CORS configuration
#    - Check backend is running: curl http://localhost:8080/api/health
#    - See README.md troubleshooting section for more help
#
# 4. Production builds:
#    - Use .env.production for production configuration
#    - Never commit sensitive data (API keys, secrets) to .env files
#    - Use environment variables in your deployment platform
#
